[{"id":"VR726248","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two views of a torsion pendulum that consists of a vertical wire connected to a horizontal disk at its center. An arrow labeled F sub 0 indicates a force applied tangentially to the disk, which creates an angular displacement of theta sub max of the disk.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR726248.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A torsion pendulum consists of a vertical wire connected to a uniform disk of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub D\"><math alttext=\"m sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub D\"><math alttext=\"r sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and rotational inertia <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end sub, squared\"><math alttext=\"one half m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end sub, squared\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><msup><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><mn>2</mn></msup></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. An applied force of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub 0\"><math alttext=\"F sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is applied tangentially to the disk, holding it in place at an angular displacement <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub max\"><math alttext=\"theta sub max\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub></math></span></span> from the wire’s relaxed angular position. The applied force is then removed, and the disk undergoes rotational simple harmonic motion. What is the angular acceleration of the disk when its angular displacement from equilibrium is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction theta sub max over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction theta sub max over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>θ</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR726248_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0\"><math alttext=\"0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, one half, close parenthesis, times the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, one half, close parenthesis, times the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>)</mo></mrow><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 times the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"2 times the fraction F sub 0 over m sub D, end sub, r sub D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]